<br>
introvert: To concentrate (one's interests) upon oneself.<br>
anti-social: Holding disdain for conversation with others.<br>
<br>
Some people like to keep their thoughts and feelings to themself in conversations and that is what an introvert is. There's nothing wrong with that, but it is felt that an anti-social, or not willing to partake in conversation behavior, can be a harmful thing.<br>
<br>
How harmful can be anyone's guess, but most anti-socials I know in real life or even online are very lonely people. Most play on computers, work a lot, read, or do some kind of activity to keep themself active or unoccupied by lonely thoughts.<br>
