Well, I myself, am an extrovert and always have been sociable. I like greeting people I come across on a daily basis and make "small talk" to let them know that I appreciate their presence. But at the same time I can appreciate introverts. Hell, half of my family are introverts, I just so happened to be the "mutant" if you will. In Laogheire's case, perhaps the computer guy greeted you as his way of letting you know that he appreciates your presence, and the protection it provides. <br>
